    "Evaluation": {
      "text": "X-ray (\nnote: imaging is often normal with this injury\n)\nPA - Widening of the triquetrolunate joint space\nLateral - volar intercalated segment instability is seen\nLunate tilts palmar producing zigzag pattern (opposite of scapholunate injury)",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Management": {
      "text": "Ulnar gutter splint\nor short arm posterior mold\nRefer to orthopedic surgery",
